Sciences-Urbana             Get research help online    If you need help with your research or assignments when you are off-campus, there are several ways our librarians can help you from a distance.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Access library resources from off-campus    Current UIC affiliates (students, faculty and staff) can access University Library resources from remote computers, either by using a Proxy URL or a Virtual Private Network ( VPN ). Either solution will allow authentication for articles in PubMed, Google Scholar and JSTOR, as well as for other Library-subscribed databases and journals.  Alumni and unaffiliated users cannot remotely access library electronic resources. Please visit the University Library in person for access.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Alumni services    If you graduated from UIC or John Marshall Law School and live in Illinois, you may be eligible for an Alumni Borrowing card to continue to check out materials from the Library.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana             Set up a library account    UIC students, faculty and staff have automatic access to UIC Library resources. Alumni and visitors can apply for borrowing cards.    Richard J. Daley Library  Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago  Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria  Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford  Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana          Filter by Location     Chicago-Daley     Chicago-Health Sciences     Peoria-Health Sciences